description: Changed default cloudChannel to '5'. This change is only relevant if you use the 'cloud' version of TinyMCE, i.e., don't host it yourself. The change 'upgrades' TinyMCE to version 5 (see changes here https://www.tiny.cloud/docs/release-notes/release-notes50/). If you want to continue to use TinyMCE version 4, initialize the editor with a specific channel: <Editor  init={{ cloudChannel: '4' }} />
